“I couldn’t tell him ‘You won’t be able to be a father first,’” he said.
“I held his hand when he stopped breathing and only after he stopped breathing and died did I finally accept that he was not invincible,” he said.
The following year, Daley competed at the 2012 Olympics and won the bronze medal.
"I knew I had dreamed of this for a lifetime, jumping in front of the spectators in my country at the Olympics, there is no feeling more beautiful," he said.
This also inspired him in the chosen music, Proud by Heather Small, a song that encouraged him before the Olympics and still excites him.
