How can the trade war between the United States and China benefit Beijing?
The oaths that announced the start of the trade war between the United States and China have been daunting and, although there seems to be a long way to go before it ends, the disputes between the two countries could be beneficial for Beijing in the long run, experts say.
U.S. President Donald Trump issued his first warning earlier this year by imposing tariffs on key imports from China, including solar panels, steel and aluminum.
The biggest escalation came this week with new taxes affecting $200 billion (<0xC2><0xA3>150 billion) worth of goods, effectively charging taxes on half of all goods in China entering the United States.
Beijing has retaliated each time, most recently by imposing a 5 to 10 percent tax on US products worth $60 billion.
